<!--Senior Eighth Rank--><!--Senior Eighth Rank--><!--Ranklist: {{ill|Senior First Rank|ja|正一位|1=Senior First Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|Junior First Rank|ja|従一位|1=Junior First Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|Senior Second Rank|ja|正二位|1=Senior Second Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|Junior Second Rank|ja|従二位|1=Junior Second Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|Senior Third Rank|ja|正三位|1=Senior Third Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|Junior Third Rank|ja|従三位|1=Junior Third Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|Senior Fourth Rank|ja|正四位|1=Senior Fourth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|Junior Fourth Rank|ja|従四位|1=Junior Fourth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|Senior Fifth Rank|ja|正五位|1=Senior Fifth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|Junior Fifth Rank|ja|従五位|1=Junior Fifth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|Senior Sixth Rank|ja|正六位|1=Senior Sixth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|Junior Sixth Rank|ja|従六位|1=Junior Sixth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|Senior Seventh Rank|ja|正七位|1=Senior Seventh Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|Junior Seventh Rank|ja|従七位|1=Junior Seventh Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|Senior Eighth Rank|ja|正八位|1=Senior Eighth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|Junior Eighth Rank|ja|従八位|1=Junior Eighth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|Senior Ninth Rank|ja|正九位|1=Senior Ninth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|Junior Ninth Rank|ja|従九位|1=Junior Ninth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|Greater Initial Rank|ja|大初位|1=Greater Initial Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|Lesser Initial Rank|ja|少初位|1=Lesser Initial Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} endRanklist--><!--Senior Eighth Rank-->

{{No footnotes|date=2015th year 8月}}

'''Shōhachi-i''' (正八位) is one of the {{ill|Court Ranks of Japan|ja|位階|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. It is positioned below {{ill|Junior Seventh Rank|ja|従七位|1=Junior Seventh Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and above {{ill|Junior Eighth Rank|ja|従八位|1=Junior Eighth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.<ref>https://www.wakapoetry.net/background/society/court-offices-titles-and-Ranks/court-Ranks/</ref>

In the {{ill|Ritsuryō system|ja|律令制|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Shōhachi-i was further divided into two subRanks: Upper Shōhachi-i (正八位上) and Lower Shōhachi-i (正八位下). During the early {{ill|Meiji period|ja|明治時代|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, under the {{ill|Daijōkan system (Meiji period)|ja|太政官制|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, these subRanks were eliminated. Shōhachi-i corresponded to positions such as assistant scribes (権少史) in the {{ill|Jingikan|ja|神祇官|1=Department of Divinities|blank= (明治時代)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and chief clerks ({{ill|Shuki|ja|主記|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) in the {{ill|Daijōkan|ja|太政官 (明治時代)|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.

Under the honor system established by the {{ill|Joi Jōrei|ja|叙位条例|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (Imperial Edict No. 10 of 1887) and the {{ill|Ikai-ryō|ja|位階令|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (Imperial Edict No. 325 of 1926), Shōhachi-i was the Rank immediately above the lowest Rank, {{ill|Jūhachi-i|ja|従八位|1=Junior Eighth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, in the hierarchy of {{ill|Court Ranks of Japan|ja|位階|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.

