 Seventh Rank|ja|正七位|1=Senior Seventh Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Seventh Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Seventh Rank|qq=}} {{ill|Junior Seventh Rank|ja|従七位|1=Junior Seventh Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Seventh Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Seventh Rank|qq=}} {{ill|Senior Eighth Rank|ja|正八位|1=Senior Eighth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Eighth Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Eighth Rank|qq=}} {{ill|Junior Eighth Rank|ja|従八位|1=Junior Eighth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Eighth Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Eighth Rank|qq=}} {{ill|Senior Ninth Rank|ja|正九位|1=Senior Ninth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Ninth Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Ninth Rank|qq=}} {{ill|Junior Ninth Rank|ja|従九位|1=Junior Ninth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Ninth Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Ninth Rank|qq=}} {{ill|Greater Initial Rank|ja|大初位|1=Greater Initial Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Greater Initial Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Greater Initial Rank|qq=}} {{ill|Lesser Initial Rank|ja|少初位|1=Lesser Initial Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Lesser Initial Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Lesser Initial Rank|qq=}} endRanklist--><!--Senior Eighth Rank-->

{{No footnotes|date=2015th year 8月}}

'''Shōhachi-i''' (正八位) is one of the {{ill|Court Ranks in Japan|ja|位階|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Court Ranks of Japan|qq=}}. It is positioned below {{ill|Junior Seventh Rank|ja|従七位|1=Junior Seventh Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Seventh Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Seventh Rank|qq=}} and above {{ill|Junior Eighth Rank|ja|従八位|1=Junior Eighth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Eighth Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Eighth Rank|qq=}}.<ref>https://www.wakapoetry.net/background/society/court-offices-titles-and-Ranks/court-Ranks/</ref>

In the [[:en:Ritsuryō|Ritsuryō system]], Shōhachi-i was further divided into two subRanks: Upper Shōhachi-i (正八位上) and Lower Shōhachi-i (正八位下). During the early [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji period]], under the {{ill|Daijōkan system (Meiji period)|ja|太政官制|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Daijōkan system (Meiji period)|qq=}}, these subRanks were eliminated. Shōhachi-i corresponded to positions such as assistant scribes (権少史) in the [[:en:Department of Divinities|Department of Divinities]] and chief clerks ({{ill|Shuki|ja|主記|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shuki|qq=}}) in the {{ill|Daijōkan|ja|太政官 (明治時代)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Daijōkan|qq=}}.

Under the honor system established by the {{ill|Joi Jōrei|ja|叙位条例|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Joi Jōrei|qq=}} (Imperial Edict No. 10 of 1887) and the {{ill|Ikai-ryō|ja|位階令|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ikai-ryō|qq=}} (Imperial Edict No. 325 of 1926), Shōhachi-i was the Rank immediately above the lowest Rank, {{ill|Jūhachi-i|ja|従八位|1=Junior Eighth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jūhachi-i|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Eighth Rank|qq=}}, in the hierarchy of {{ill|Court Ranks in Japan|ja|位階|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Court Ranks of Japan|qq=}}.

